  "text": "Cyst formation was induced as described by [CITATION_1] , by aerobic mainte- Table I . C and N spectra of Rhodocista strains. Aerobic growth in liquid cultures (5 ml on a rotary shaker) was conducted with cells pre-grown in an ammonium/acetate medium and washed twice with water to remove all nutrients. Anaerobic growth in liquid cultures (8 ml screw cap bottles without gas phase) was conducted with cells treated as above. Vitamins were supplied as required (see Table II ). Results in square brackets are from [CITATION_2] nance for several days at 42 ∞C on plates containing NH 4 Cl and butyrate as N and C sources, respectively. Their development closely followed the pattern as cited above: after 1 d some cells began to swell (Fig. 2c) and finally formed tetrads like R. centenaria (Figs. 2d, e) . These cysts resumed vegetative growth when cultivated at optimum temperatures.",
